<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1406,957,1199]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Diagnosis: Metacoxa with horn-shaped meracanthus, metatibia usually with grouped apical spurs, metabasitarsus usually with 
<number box="[467,481,1066,1090]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
lateral spurs. Larva bearing triangular, petiolate tarsal arolium; often with capitate setae and sectasetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1406,957,1199]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Internal relationships: The 
<taxonomicName box="[525,628,1139,1163]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Psyllidae</taxonomicName>
contains five probably monophyletic subfamilies. The phylogenetic relationships between them are unknown.
</paragraph>
